body:
When I build use default `VM_PARALLEL_BUILDS` make flag, the Verilator run will fail with the following error message.
```
dyld[28472]: symbol not found in flat namespace '_hello'
zsh: abort      ./obj_dir/Vtop
```
But when I build with `-MAKEFLAGS VM_PARALLEL_BUILDS=0`, the Verilator run works fine.

- Can you attach an example that shows the issue?  (Must be openly licensed, ideally in test_regress format.)

```cpp
// py_dpi.cpp
#include <pybind11/pybind11.h>
#include <pybind11/embed.h>
#include "svdpi.h"

extern "C" {

namespace py = pybind11;

void hello();

PYBIND11_MODULE(py_dpi, m) {
    m.doc() = "svuvm api module";

    m.def("hello", &hello, "suspend the simulation");

}

}
```

